# Supabase — copy to `.env` and fill from your project's API settings.
# Both values are safe in the client (anon key is public; RLS enforces access).
# When these are set, the admin uses the Supabase backend; when absent it falls
# back to browser localStorage.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# Optional: Vercel Deploy Hook for the marketing site. When set, saving a
# product or category pings this URL so the website rebuilds and its prerendered
# SEO/JSON-LD catches up with the live catalogue. Create one at Vercel → Project
# → Settings → Git → Deploy Hooks. Leave blank to disable (the live site still
# updates instantly in the browser regardless).
VITE_DEPLOY_HOOK_URL=

# NOTE: the AI product copywriter needs GEMINI_API_KEY, but it is NOT a VITE_
# var — it must stay server-side. Set it as a Supabase Edge Function secret:
#   supabase functions deploy product-copywriter
#   supabase secrets set GEMINI_API_KEY=your-google-ai-studio-key
#   (optional) supabase secrets set GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-flash-lite-latest
